      "id": "assistant-1774982817903-csfqmz",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Great — with storyboard and character sheets both holding, I moved the project into keyframe planning.\n\nI mapped the sequence into **10 keyframes total**, with a **start and end frame for each of the 5 shots**. That’s the right choice here because the scene is subtle, but each beat still has a meaningful emotional shift:\n\n- **Shot 01**: room and relationship established\n- **Shot 02**: panda begins speaking, then lands the confession\n- **Shot 03**: psychologist listens, then asks the redirecting question\n- **Shot 04**: panda absorbs the question, then admits “Neither”\n- **Shot 05**: shared frame reunites them, then lands the hopeful final line\n\nThe overall shape is strong: observational at first, then progressively tighter and more intimate, ending in a shared frame instead of a punchline button.\n\nNext, the natural move is to prepare the actual **keyframe prompts** for generation. After that, you’ll need to run the image generation step so we can review the still anchors before moving into motion."
    },
